# Tech Stack and UI Conventions

## Core stack

- Framework: Angular (standalone components, TypeScript, reactive forms).
- Styling: Tailwind utility classes as default.
- UI primitives/components: Spartan (`@spartan-ng/helm` + local wrappers in `src/app/shared/ui/*`).
- State pattern: feature stores using `@ngrx/signals`.
- Runtime persistence: Supabase (`@supabase/supabase-js`) with Auth + Postgres + RLS.
- Schema/migrations: Drizzle ORM (`drizzle-orm` + `drizzle-kit`) with repository abstraction.

## Data and state conventions

- Use Signal Store (`signalStore`, `withState`, `withComputed`, `withMethods`) for feature state management.
- Keep async CRUD and mutation orchestration in feature stores, not in templates.
- Keep persistence access in repository classes; page and presentational components must not access storage directly.
- Use Supabase client in repositories for runtime CRUD; keep `user_id` ownership aligned with RLS.
- Use Drizzle schema/migrations for data model evolution and keep model/mapper/repository contracts aligned.
- Current form baseline is reactive forms. For future Angular upgrades, periodically re-evaluate Angular Signal Forms (experimental in Angular 21+) for fit, migration effort, and stability before adopting.

## UI implementation defaults

- Prefer Tailwind utilities in templates for layout/spacing/visual tweaks.
- Do not introduce plain CSS for routine component styling when Tailwind utilities are sufficient.
- Prefer `@spartan-ng/helm` wrappers/primitives and `@ng-icons/*` icons over native HTML elements whenever an equivalent exists.
- Do not introduce native controls (`<select>`, raw menu patterns, ad-hoc table controls, custom inline SVG icons, etc.) when Spartan + ng-icons can cover the same interaction.
- If no clear Spartan equivalent exists for the needed behavior, stop and ask the user for direction before implementing a native/custom fallback.
  - Example: use Spartan combobox/sheet/context-menu/table/button/input wrappers and ng-icons icon sets instead of custom-built alternatives.

## Shared component boundary

- `src/app/shared/ui/`:
  - Reserved for Spartan wrappers/primitives and low-level UI directives.
- `src/app/shared/components/`:
  - Reusable app-level presentational components composed from those wrappers.

## Refactor guardrails

- Preserve existing UX and behavior while refactoring.
- Keep page files as orchestration containers; extract presentational pieces into components.
- Favor incremental, verifiable changes with build/tests after substantial edits.
